Secretary of Transportation Pete Buttigieg, National Economic Council Director Brian Deese, and National Climate Advisor Gina McCarthy recently met with automotive industry manufacturers and labor leaders to discuss priorities related to economic recovery, job creation, and addressing the climate crisis. The officials highlighted President Biden's commitment to investing in the automotive industry to create well-paying union jobs and transition to clean energy. They also emphasized the administration's plan to use the federal government's purchasing power to support clean energy industries and strengthen domestic supply chains. The participants in the meeting shared their perspectives and ideas, and the officials expressed their commitment to continue working together towards economic recovery and a clean energy future.